      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "5000-sample Monte Carlo sweep over inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity. 95th-percentile hemolysis index remains below clinical threshold at 4 of 5 operating points.",
